The paper deals with improving algorithms for approximating shortest paths in the Congested Clique model of distributed computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves designing new algorithms for computing sparse emulators and distance-sensitive variants for the distance tool-kit, which are topics in the areas of Algorithms (cs.AL) and Data Structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions a derandomization scheme for a variant of the hitting set problem, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper involves working with graphs and computing distances, which are topics in Computational Geometry (cs.CG).
